DAILY POST brings you the results of all the 2022 UEFA Nations League matches that took place on Tuesday. Hungary defeated England 4-0 at the Molineux Stadium. A brace from Roland Sallai and a strike each from Zsolt Nagy and Daniel Gazdag ensured Hungary won against the Three Lions. Below are the results of the games played on Tuesday:
A3 England 0-4 Hungary
A3 Germany 5-2 Italy
A4 Netherlands 3-2 Wales
A4 Poland 0-1 Belgium
B1 Armenia 1-4 Scotland
B1 Ukraine 1-1 Republic of Ireland
B3 Bosnia and Herzegovina 3-2 Finland
B3 Romania 0-3 Montenegro
C1 Luxembourg 2-2 Faroe Islands
C1 Türkiye 2-0 Lithuania
D1 Moldova 2-1 Andorra
D1 Liechtenstein 0-2 Latvia Meanwhile, match day five fixtures will continue on Thursday, 22 September:
